    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-21T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–2144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-21T19:00:00+07:00"
                            >July 21, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 22—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1264. Hollington Tong<note n="41" xml:id="d122fn41">Chinese Vice Minister of
                        Information.</note> spoke casually to the Counselor at a dinner party in
                    regard to subject of Department’s 966, July 17. He said he had exchanged
                    telegrams with Lattimore<note n="42" xml:id="d122fn42">Owen Lattimore, Deputy
                        Director of Pacific Operations, Office of War Information.</note> (through
                    OWI Department doubtless having seen the messages) and he was wondering whether
                    it would not be best just to drop the matter. Atcheson replied in affirmative,
                    pointing out that it was much better to let it drop than to give the article
                    emphasis and additional publicity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
